Notice that most of the dialogue in most of the superhero movies is no bueno?

It doesn’t have to be.  They just need to do the work.

It’s not a difficult language register to write.  It’s actually easy.  It’s every day talk.

But they always overdo it, not do it.

As an example is VENOM, GoftheG2.  Just no bueno.

I just saw SPIDERUNIVERSE and that is a good example of how to write for a comic book movie.  The older Spider-Man sounded like an older Spider-Man.  Gwen talked like a girl of her age.  And the young spiderman sounded like a teenager.

The movie was muy awesome because it was a moving comic book with boxes that read ELSEWHERE just like in the comic books.  That is a very simple and good way to advance plot, edit and transition from one place to another.

Anyways, I hope they get it right.


And can’t W8 for ALITA.   James Cameron, bitches!

comment:
Just saw the movie. (A very honest review)
First half was disappointing with awful storytelling. Nicole is awesome. That aquarium scene is badass. But the chase scene in Italy, it was disappointing because of the pathetic background music. The script really could've been better in the first half. When Mera takes Arthur in her ship, the VFX didn't really impress me at all, not because it was bad, it's everything but bad, but because the story, those moments weren't at all compelling, engaging for the audience that I didn't even feel like I should appreciate those great effects. The first half barely impressed me. There were some fun moments. It's watchable. 
The second half is like a whole different movie. My goodness!!! Right after they go to the trench for the Trident, the movie is gold. Perfect. The story, all the moments are engaging, compelling, you're thrilled to see every scene. To see Arthur meeting his mom, to see King Atlan, to see Arthur getting the trident, to see him in his fucking suit. That suit is a piece of work. The suit is fucking awesome. No character in the comic book movies has a suit that looks so good and so badass at the same time. No character has that. And everything after is awesome. Literally everything. The 3rd act/climax is the biggest and the best of all Superhero movies (Marvel and DC both). I literally wanted to jump off my seat. Arthur was so freaking badass. They legitimately made Aquaman look cool, like the coolest hero in the big screen in this climax. This is the vibe the superhero movies should give. And the CGI effects in the final ORM vs King Arthur fight. HOLY FUCK!!! It was like that scene was taken out from some epic video game with great graphics. And in the end, when Aquaman swims above and floats in the air, that's like the coolest thing I've ever seen. That was fucking badass. 

This movie is big. This movie is ambitious. It isn't perfect, but it's fucking awesome. Almost all the time, the superhero movies have a disappointing climax. This movie has the greatest final fight of all time.
7/10 from me. I don't believe Aquaman wasn't nominated for the 2019 Visual Effects Oscar. They did watch the movie in 2d? Black Panther and Ant-man got nominated instead? WTF do these people smoke?

comment: I watched the movie on Wednesday 12/12/18. It is very entertaining. It doesn't have the amazing story line of Avengers Infinity War, which is why DCEU compensated by putting in a lot of action and humour. However, Jason Mamoa and the delicious Amber Heard put in fantastic performances. The CGI is also very good. Just make sure you don't watch it on an old 1080p cinema screen. I did, which is why the ticket was so cheap (£5). This film is definitely worth watching. I look forward to it coming out on 4k. There are also some silly parts in the film such as the pirate who knows how to rebuild Atlantean battle suits, but looking at the larger picture, it is a minor niggle.

comment: Saw it. 3/10 for superhero movies lol. The trailer shows every fight scene. There's nothing new to see. This is a common ploy to attract naive adults and children. The dialogue is terrible. There's tonnes of unnecessary narration just like 'The last Airbender' to help try and plug the wholes of this sinking titanic. Aquaman kills innocent people in cold blood. Not very hero like at all. He's one dimensional and cracks cheesy unnecessary one liners that don't make you cringe. There's terrible music the chimes in and out of each fight scene. The whole movie plays like a parody of itself.  I'm serious! The whole movie is in the trailer. It's a trick to make the gullible think there might be loads more fight scenes and plot twists but there isn't. If you've watched the trailer, you've watched the movie. Another DC abomination! comment:
Saw it. Excellent. 8/10 for superhero movies. This trailer doesn’t show much compared to the actual film. Better than BvS and Justice League. The dialogue is not Marvel-level but I was very surprised by how this movie turned out. DCEU should have just done the origins movies first for Aquaman,Cyborg, Flash. You can tell Aquaman was supposed to be released before JL a couple of reshot scenes just casually mentions steppenwolf and the other Justice league members are not referenced in this movie at all. That’s hard to skip over since they try to make it seem as Aquaman is new to his roots when they had him already talking with mera in JL. So it’s a excellent movie just not the well planned process  that is the  MCU.
Black Manta is wicked and his origin in Aquaman is well done and actually makes sense.

comment:
I don't really understand why they went with the classic orange and green outfit... Maybe it'll look better when I see it in motion, but it just looks kinda silly to me right now.  Some comicbook suits just don't work on the big screen.  If this movie took place before Justice League, I could understand them using the classic suit as his first suit,  but after doing some reading into it, I found that this movie takes place after Justice League.  And the suit he had in Justice League I thought looked badass while also reminiscent to classic suit.  Of all the things people complained about in Justice League, not one complaint was about Aquaman's armor, so why change it?
Unless the classic suit serves as part of the origin story in this movie, the change makes no sense to me unless they're just pandering to the hardcore nerd audience.
